<item>
<emph2>
August
</emph2> begins on the same day of the week as 
<emph2>
February
</emph2> in a leap year.
</item></normallist><p>
In the United States, there are no national holidays or other commonly celebrated events during August. In 
<collectionlink xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="26667.xml">
Spain
</collectionlink>, August is the holiday month for most workers.
</p><normallist>
<item>
August's 
<collectionlink xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="36962.xml">
flower
</collectionlink> is the 
<collectionlink xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="161758.xml">
poppy
</collectionlink>.
</item><item>
August's 
<unknownlink src="birthstone">
birthstone
</unknownlink> is the 
<collectionlink xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="45162.xml">
peridot
</collectionlink>.
</item></normallist><template name="months">
